# Xcode build / test ‚Äî only when asked

**Do not run `xcodebuild`** (`clean`, `build`, `build-for-testing`, or `test`) proactively after code changes, feature work, bug fixes, or test authoring ‚Äî even when you added or updated tests.

The user prefers **not** to wait on frequent test runs. **Author tests in code; do not execute them** unless one of the triggers below applies.

## When to run

Run the Xcode workflow (**`.cursor/rules/xcode-run-test.mdc`**) **only** when:

1. **Explicit test / build / run request** ‚Äî the user asks to **run**, **launch**, **build**, **test**, **‚åòU**, verify compile, rebuild on Dre's phone, or similar. Device runs use **`.cursor/rules/xcode-run-dres-phone.mdc`**.
2. **Commit and/or push** ‚Äî the user asks to **`git commit`**, **`git push`**, or ship / commit-and-push. **Before** staging or committing, run the pre-check on **iPhone 17 simulator** (`platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17,OS=latest` per **`xcode-run-test.mdc`**): **`clean`** ‚Üí **`clean build-for-testing`** ‚Üí **`test`**.
   - Fix compile errors, failing tests, regressions you introduced, and **all project build warnings** (**`xcode-fix-build-warnings.mdc`**); repeat until green.
   - **Do not commit or push** until **BUILD SUCCEEDED**, **all tests pass**, and **project warning count is 0**.

## When not to run

- After implementing or fixing something ‚Äî **never** ‚Äújust to verify‚Äù or ‚Äúto confirm‚Äù your work.
- At handoff when the user did not ask to test, build, commit, or push.
- Because **`code-changes-require-tests.mdc`** asked you to **write** tests ‚Äî writing tests does **not** require executing **`xcodebuild`**.
- Multiple times in the same session unless the user asks again or a new commit/push request requires a fresh pre-check.

## Handoff without a build

When finishing work without a test/build/commit request, skip build logs and do not claim **BUILD SUCCEEDED** / **FAILED**. Tell the user what changed; they can ask to test or commit when ready.
